data.text: The Skylands Stadium is a baseball arena that was established in the year 1994 and owned by Al Dorso. It was constructed with a natural grass surface which makes it easier for players to run and skid. Over the years it has been the home ground to a number of teams like Sussex Skyhawks, Newark Bears, New Jersey Cardinals and many more.
